Mohammed Aminu of Bauchi Golf Club made a record becoming the youngest professional golfer in the register of Professional Golfers Association of Nigeria (PGAN) at the recent 2018 Qualifying School resits examination in Jos, Plateau State. The Bauchi Golf Club product, made his professional debut in the inaugural 2018 Kadinvest Open, which held from March 27-30 Kaduna Golf Club and not without some lessons which will help reshape his golf career. Aminu 21 and a Business Administration student of Abubakar Tatari Ali Polytechnic Bauchi revealed to DAILY INDEPENDENT that it takes more of focus, courage and commitment for a first timer to survive the scare of playing alongside senior professionals. The former Nigeria Junior champions speaking further on the journey so far said: “I felt so intimidated in my first tournament in Kaduna (Kadinvest). “I was afraid; it took the understanding of the senior professionals to help me out with words of encouragement. But, at the time I regained my confidence, it was too late for good a good score,” he explained. Aminu who is looking forward to the next Governor’s Cup tournament in Jigawa State said, “The most important thing is that I have learnt a lot of lessons from Kadinvest. I’ll be in Jigawa for the Governor’s Cup and I hope to do better.” 0 comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE.  100% Natural Solution To Premature Ejaculation, Weak Erection, Watery Sperm, Other Sexual Dysfunctions And Last More Than 30 Minutes During Sex.